Introduction

Highlight (formerly known as BEAST) is a four-member boy group under Around US Entertainment. They debuted on October 16, 2009, with the mini album 'Beast Is The B2ST.'

After their seven-year contracts with Cube Entertainment had ended, they decided not to renew them. Then, they established their own agency called Around US Entertainment. On February 24, 2017, Around US announced they had changed their name to Highlight, which is also the title of their final album under Cube. They released their first mini-album Can You Feel It? on March 20 of the same year.

In March 2019, member Junhyung got involved in an adult-related scandal. Following that on March 14, 2019, Junhyung apologized for his actions and announced his departure from Highlight.

On April 2, Around Us Entertainment announced that they reached a mutual agreement regarding the use of the trademark rights for the name BEAST. Nevertheless, the group will continue promoting under the name Highlight. With this agreement, Highlight has regained full rights to BEAST's name and discography, meaning their past releases under BEAST are now officially under their control.
